data.title: 1 Events: 1.2 February
data.meta_description:
1928 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document summarizes key events that occurred in 1928. Some of the major events included:

1) In January, convicted murderer Ruth Snyder was executed at Sing Sing prison in New York. Leon Trotsky was also exiled from Moscow to Central Asia. 

2) The first ever separate Winter Olympics were held in February in St. Moritz, Switzerland. 

3) In March, the St. Francis Dam in California failed, killing over 600 people in one of the worst civil engineering disasters in U.S. history. 

4) Throughout the year there were numerous other political, scientific, and transportation developments across the world, including the beginnings of regular television programming and important aviation records being set.
